{{Dinka name|Aluck}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Aluck Akech | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = Aluck Akech with [[Al-Merreikh SC|Merreikh]] | fullname = Aluck Akech Mabior | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1994|02|8}} | birth_place = [[Aweil]], [[Sudan]] (now [[South Sudan]]) | height = {{convert|1.85|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[Al-Merreikh SC]] | clubnumber = 17 | youthyears1 = 2010–2012 |youthclubs1 = [[Aweil Stars F.C.|Aweil Stars]] | youthyears2 = 2012–2013 |youthclubs2 = [[Salaam Aweil F.C.|Salaam Aweil]] | youthyears3 = 2013–2014 |youthclubs3 = [[Al-Malakia FC|Malakia]] | years1 = 2010–2011 |clubs1 = [[Aweil Stars F.C.|Aweil Stars]] |caps1 = 12 |goals1 = 19 | years2 = 2012–2013 |clubs2 = [[Salaam Aweil F.C.|Salaam Aweil]] |caps2 = 31 |goals2 = 24 | years3 = 2014–2014 |clubs3 = [[Al-Malakia FC|Malakia]] |caps3 = 40 |goals3 = 6 | years4 = 2014–2015 |clubs4 = [[Al-Merreikh Kosti]] | caps4 = 2 |goals4 = 3 | years5 = 2015– |clubs5 = [[Al-Merreikh SC]] | caps5 = 1 |goals5 = 2 | nationalteam-update = 24 May 2017 | nationalyears1 = 2014&ndash; |nationalteam1 = [[South Sudan national football team|South Sudan]] |nationalcaps1 = 9 |nationalgoals1 = 0 }}
'''Aluck Akech Mabior''' (born February 8, 1994),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.joueurs.aluck-akech.mabior.231513.en.html/|title=Aluck Akech Mabior|website=footballdatabase.eu|access-date=2018-05-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soccerpunter.com/players/407181-Akech-Aluck/|title=Akech Mabior Aluck - Profile and Statistics - SoccerPunter.com|website=www.soccerpunter.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-21}}</ref> known as '''Aluck Akech''' ([[Aweil, South Sudan]]), also spelled as '''Aluk Akec''' in [[Dinka language]], is a [[South Sudan]]ese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Sudan]]ese club [[Al-Merreikh SC]]. Aluck started his football career as street football in the [[Sudan]] before [[South Sudan]] gained its independence. In 2009 Aluck returned to the south, and [[Aweil Stars F.C.|Aweil Stars]] administrators realised that Aluck was footballer and that great realisation brought them to registration of Aluck. And in the year 2012 Aluck joined [[Salaam Aweil F.C.|Salaam Aweil]] from Aweil Stars. And he spent two years with Salaam Aweil than Salaam Aweil sold him to [[Al-Malakia FC|Malakia]] in 2014. When Aluck was playing in [[Juba]] (the South Sudanese capital) for Malakia; [[South Sudan national football team]] administrators realized that he was capable for [[South Sudan national football team]]. And Malakia sold him to [[Sudan]]ese club Al-Merreikh Costi in 2014. And Merreikh Kosti sold him to [[Al-Merreikh SC]].
== South Sudan national football team == {{Main article|South Sudan national football team}} <!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Aluck Akech with South Sudan.jpeg|thumb|Aluck stands in front of his goalkeeper Juma (Aluck Akech with [[South Sudan national football team|South Sudan]] playing against [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] on September 5, 2015 at [[Juba]] stadium)]] --> Aluck first started his national games with [[South Sudan national football team|South Sudan]] faced [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]], [[Mali national football team|Mali]], [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] and [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]]. Aluck is the first South Sudanese player who was given red card in the [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] record in [[Nouakchott]] the [[Mauritania]]n capital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soccerpunter.com/players/407181-Akech-Aluck/|title=Akech Mabior Aluck - Profile and Statistics - SoccerPunter.com|website=www.soccerpunter.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://hotinjuba.com/mauritania-humiliates-bright-stars-in-a-4-0-defeat/|title=Mauritania humiliates Bright Stars in a 4-0 defeat|date=2015-10-14|work=Hot in Juba|access-date=2018-05-21|language=en-US}}</ref> On September 4, 2016 Aluck was included in the squad of South Sudan against [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] in last match of [[South Sudan national football team|South Sudan]] in the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group C]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201609010071.html/|title=Africa: South Sudan Names 23-Man Squad for Equatorial Guinea Reverse|date=2016-09-01|work=Confederation of African Football (Giza)|access-date=2018-05-21}}</ref>
===Al-Merreikh SC=== Aluck was signed by [[Sudan|Sudanese]] club [[Al-Merreikh|Merreikh]] Omdurman-based club in 2015 and was said registered as a local Sudanese player despite representing South Sudan at international level. The Sudan Football Association have largely banned him from playing in that year, [[Sudan Premier League]] until the matter is resolved.<ref>[http://talkofjuba.com/article/row-over-citizenship-south-sudanese-footballer-khartoum/ Al-Merreikh SC] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160710001443/http://talkofjuba.com/article/row-over-citizenship-south-sudanese-footballer-khartoum/ |date=July 10, 2016 }}</ref>
